==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ionize
<hw>ionize</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physics,
Chemistry)</fld> <def>to dissociate into ions, as by dissolution in
water or another polar solvent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ionize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: ionize
<hw>i"on*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Ionized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Ionizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Physics,
Chemistry)</fld> <def>To convert (an atom or molecule) into ions, e. g.
by dissolving in water, by reaction with acid or alkali, or by
interaction with ionizing radiation. See <er>ionization</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ionized</ent>⟦br⟧
